# Day 1-4 | Android & Kotlin Fundamentals

## Overview

The first few days were focused on setting up my Android development environment, choosing learning resources, and building a solid foundation in Kotlin and Android basics.

## Topics Covered

### Kotlin Fundamentals
- Variables and data types
- Numbers (Int, Double, Float)
- Strings and Booleans
- Type conversion
- Arrays
- Lists
- Sets
- Maps
- Operators
- If / When
- Loops (for, while)
- Functions
- User input
- Return values
- Classes
- Constructors
- Visibility modifiers
- Nullable types
- Null safety

### Android Fundamentals
- Creating Android projects
- View Binding
- Connecting UI components with Kotlin
- XML basics

### Jetpack Compose
- Created a simple Birthday Card application
- Learned the basics of Composable functions
- Preview
- Column / Row / Box
- State and layout fundamentals

## Challenges

- Choosing the right learning resources
- Understanding the differences between XML and Jetpack Compose
- Setting up Android Studio and SDK
- Running applications on an emulator and a physical device

